# AI / Cursor — takarékos kontextus

Details: **`docs/DEVELOPMENT_WORKFLOW.md` § 10** · live checklist: **`docs/live/ai-cursor-token-efficiency.md`**.

- Prefer **one scope per thread** (one iteration / PR / bug). Use **§7 Handoff** + `docs/live/03` ACTIVE line in new chats; **new chat** when the thread mixes topics or is very long.
- Attach **`@files` / folders minimally** — only what the task needs; avoid whole-repo / `@Codebase` unless necessary.
- **`.cursorignore`** (repo root) limits indexed noise — do not rely on pulling entire `bin/` / `node_modules` into context.
- For large logs: **file in repo** or **one attachment** + pointer, not pasted walls of text.
- **Composer** for multi-file / large edits; **Chat** for small single-file work when enough.
- End-of-iteration: refresh **`docs/live/02` + `03`**, **`pr-body.md`**, then **`iter-end`** / `gh` — reduces PR back-and-forth.
